
<div class="red bold">Example 4.1:</div>

<div class="l-example">
\( u^{\prime \prime}(x)=-\sin x+x-\int_{0}^{\frac{\pi}{2}} x t u(t) d t, u(0)=0, u^{\prime}(0)=1 \)
</div>

<div class="red bold">Solution 4.1:</div>

<div class="l-example">
\( u^{\prime \prime}(x)=-\sin x+x-x \int_{0}^{\frac{\pi}{2}} t u(t) d t \)
</div>

<div class="l-example">
\( u^{\prime \prime}(x)=-\sin x+x-\alpha x, \alpha=\int_{0}^{\frac{\pi}{2}} t u(t) d t \)
</div>

<div class="l-example">
\( u^{\prime \prime}(x)=-\sin x+(1-\alpha) x \)
</div>

Integrating both sides from 0 to x;

<div class="l-example">
\( u^{\prime}(x)-u^{\prime}(0)=\cos x+(1-\alpha) \frac{1}{2} x^{2} \)
</div>

<div class="l-example">
\( u^{\prime}(x)=1+\cos x+\frac{1}{2}(1-\alpha) x^{2} \), Integrating again both sides,
</div>

<div class="l-example">
\( u(x)-u(0)=x+\sin x+\frac{1}{3 !}(1-\alpha) x^{3} \)
</div>

<div class="l-example">
\( * u(x)=x+\sin x+\frac{1}{3 !}(1-\alpha) x^{3} \) <i>and</i> \( u(t)=t+\sin t+\frac{1}{3 !}(1-\alpha) t^{3} \)
</div>

<div class="l-example">
\( \alpha=\int_{0}^{\frac{\pi}{2}} t\left(t+\sin t+\frac{1}{3 !}(1-\alpha) t^{3}\right) d t \Rightarrow \alpha=\int_{0}^{\frac{\pi}{2}}\left(t^{2}+t \sin t+\frac{1}{3 !}(1-\alpha) t^{4}\right) d t \)
</div>

<div class="l-example">
\( \Rightarrow \alpha=\left.\left(\frac{1}{3} t^{3}+\sin t-t . \cos t+\frac{1}{3 !} . \frac{1}{5}(1-\alpha) t^{5}\right)\right|_{t=0} ^{\frac{\pi}{2}} \)
</div>

<div class="l-example">
\( \Rightarrow \alpha=\frac{\pi^{3}}{24}+1-0+\frac{1}{30}(1-\alpha) \frac{\pi^{5}}{32} \Rightarrow \alpha=\frac{\pi^{3}}{24}+1+\frac{\pi^{5}}{30.32}-\frac{\pi^{5} \alpha}{30.32} \)
</div>

<div class="l-example">
\( \Rightarrow\left(1+\frac{\pi^{5}}{30.32}\right) \alpha=\frac{\pi^{3}}{24}+1+\frac{\pi^{5}}{30.32} \Rightarrow \frac{960+\pi^{5}}{960} \alpha=\frac{\pi^{3}}{24}+1+\frac{\pi^{5}}{960} \)
</div>

<div class="l-example">
\( \alpha=\left(\frac{\pi^{3}}{24}+1+\frac{\pi^{5}}{960}\right) . \frac{960}{960+\pi^{5}} \Rightarrow \alpha=\frac{40 \pi^{3}+960+\pi^{5}}{960+\pi^{5}} \)
</div>

<div class="l-example">
\( u(x)=x+\sin x+\frac{1}{3 !}\left(1-\frac{40 \pi^{3}+960+\pi^{5}}{960+\pi^{5}}\right) x^{3} \)
</div>

<div class="l-example">
\( u(x)=x+\sin x+\frac{1}{6}\left(\frac{-40 \pi^{3}}{960+\pi^{5}}\right) x^{3} \Rightarrow u(x)=x+\sin x-\frac{-20 \pi^{3} x^{3}}{3\left(960+\pi^{5}\right)} \)
</div>


