<div class="red bold">Example 4.3:</div>
Solve the Fredholm integro-differential equation
<span class="l-example">
\( u^{\prime \prime}(x)=e^{x}-x+x \int_{0}^{1} t u(t) d t, u(0)=1, u^{\prime}(0)=1 \)
</span>
 by reducing it to a Fredholm integral equation.

<br>
<div class="red bold">Solution 4.3:</div>

Integrating two times the given integro – differential equation gives us the corresponding Fredholm integral equation.

<div class="l-example">
\( u^{\prime}(x)-u^{\prime}(0)=e^{x}-\frac{1}{2} x^{2}+\frac{1}{2} x^{2} \int_{0}^{1} t u(t) d t \)
</div>

<div class="l-example">
\( u^{\prime}(x)=1+e^{x}-\frac{1}{2} x^{2}+\frac{1}{2} x^{2} \int_{0}^{1} t u(t) d t \)
</div>

Integrate once more,

<div class="l-example">
\( u(x)-u(0)=x+e^{x}-\frac{1}{3 !} x^{3}+\frac{1}{3 !} x^{3} \int_{0}^{1} t u(t) d t \)
</div>

<div class="l-example">
\( u(x)=1+x+e^{x}-\frac{1}{3 !} x^{3}+\frac{1}{3 !} x^{3} \underbrace{\int_{0}^{1} t u(t) d t}_{\text{Fredholm integral equation}}  \)
</div>

Let’s solve the Fredholm equation by directly computation method.


<div class="l-example">
\( u(x)=1+x+e^{x}-\frac{1}{3 !}(1-\alpha) x^{3}, \alpha=\int_{0}^{1} t u(t) d t \)
</div>


<div class="l-example">
\( u(t)=1+t+e^{t}-\frac{1}{3 !}(1-\alpha) t^{3}, \alpha=\int_{0}^{1} t\left(1+t+e^{t}-\frac{1}{3 !}(1-\alpha) t^{3}\right) d t \)
</div>

<div class="l-example">
\( \Rightarrow \alpha=\int_{0}^{1}\left(t+t^{2}+t . e^{t}-\frac{1}{3 !}(1-\alpha) t^{4}\right) d t \Rightarrow \alpha=\left.\left[\frac{t^{2}}{2}+\frac{t^{3}}{3}+(t-1) . e^{t}-\frac{1}{3 ! . 5}(1-\alpha) t^{5}\right]\right|_{0} ^{1} \)
</div>

<div class="l-example">
\( \Rightarrow \alpha=\frac{1}{2}+\frac{1}{3}-\frac{1}{30}(1-\alpha)+1 \Rightarrow \frac{11}{6}-\frac{1}{30}+\frac{\alpha}{30} \Rightarrow \frac{29}{30} \alpha=\frac{54}{30} \Rightarrow \alpha=\frac{54}{29} \)
</div>


<div class="l-example">
\( u(x)=1+x+e^{x}-\frac{1}{3 !}\left(-\frac{25}{29}\right) x^{3} \)
</div>


<div class="red bold">Example 4.4:</div>
Solve the following Volterra integro-differential equation
<span class="l-example">
\( u^{\prime \prime}(x)=x+\int_{0}^{x}(x-t) u(t) d t, u(0)=0, u^{\prime}(0)=1 \)
</span>
by using ADM.

<br>
<div class="red bold">Solution 4.4:</div>
Here n-fold integral idea will be used.

<div class="l-example">
\( L^{-1}(.)=\int_{0}^{x} \int_{0}^{x}(.) d x d x \quad\quad u(x)=\sum_{n=0}^{\infty} u_{n}(x)(A D M) \)
</div>

Integrating both sides of equation

<div class="l-example">
\( u^{\prime}(x)-u^{\prime}(0)=\frac{1}{2} x^{2}+\underbrace{\int_{0}^{x} \int_{0}^{x}(x-t) u(t) d t}_{L^{-1}\left(\int_{0}^{x}(x-t) u(t) d t\right)} \)
</div>

<div class="l-example">
\( u^{\prime}(x)-u^{\prime}(0)=\frac{1}{2} x^{2}+\int_{0}^{x} \int_{0}^{x}(x-t) u(t) d t d t \)
</div>

integrate once more

<div class="l-example">
\( u(x)-u(0)=x+\frac{1}{3 !} x^{3}+\underbrace{\int_{0}^{x} \int_{0}^{x} \int_{0}^{x}(x-t) u(t) d t d t d t}_{L^{-1}\left(\int_{0}^{x}(x-t) u(t) d t\right)=\int_{0}^{x} \int_{0}^{x}(x-t) u(t) d t d t} \)
</div>

<div class="l-example">
\( u(x)=x+\frac{1}{3 !} x^{3}+\frac{1}{2 !} \int_{0}^{x}(x-t) u(t) d t \)
</div>

<div class="l-example">
\( u(x)=x+\frac{1}{3 !} x^{3}+L^{-1}\left(\int_{0}^{x}(x-t) u(t) d t\right)=\int_{0}^{x} \int_{0}^{x}(x-t) u(t) d t d t \)
</div>

Use Adomian Decomposition Method

<div class="l-example">
\( u_{0}(x)+u_{1}(x)+u_{2}(x)+\ldots=x+\frac{1}{3 !} x^{3}+L^{-1}\left(\int_{0}^{x}(x-t)\left(u_{0}(t)+u_{1}(t)+u_{2}(t)+\ldots\right) d t\right) \)
</div>

<div class="l-example">
\( u_{0}(x)+u_{1}(x)+u_{2}(x)+\ldots=x+\frac{1}{3 !} x^{3}+L^{-1}\left(\underbrace{\int_{0}^{x}(x-t) u_{0}(t) d t}_{\text{2-fold integral}}+L^{-1}\left(\int_{0}^{x}(x-t) u_{1}(t) d t\right)\right)+\ldots \)
</div>

<div class="l-example">
\( u_{0}(x)=x+\frac{1}{3 !} x^{3} \)
</div>

<div class="l-example">
\( u_{1}(x)=L^{-1}\left(\int_{0}^{x}(x-t)\left(t+\frac{1}{6} t^{3}\right) d t\right) \Rightarrow u_{1}(x)=L^{-1}\left(\int_{0}^{x} x t+\frac{1}{6} x t^{3}-t^{2}-\frac{1}{6} t^{4}\right) d t \)
</div>

<div class="l-example">
\( u_{1}(x)=L^{-1}\left[\left.\left(\frac{x t^{2}}{2}+\frac{1}{4 !} x t^{4}-\frac{t^{3}}{3}-\frac{1}{30} t^{5}\right)\right|_{t=0} ^{x}\right] \Rightarrow u_{1}(x)=L^{-1}\left[\frac{x^{3}}{3 !}+\frac{1}{4 !} x t^{5}-\frac{x^{3}}{3}-\frac{1}{30} x^{5}\right] \)
</div>

<div class="l-example">
\( u_{1}(x)=L^{-1}\left(\frac{1}{4 ! 6} x^{6}-\frac{1}{30.6} x^{6}\right) \Rightarrow u_{1}(x)=\left(\frac{1}{4 ! 6.7} x^{7}-\frac{1}{30.6 .7} x^{7}\right) \)
</div>

